{
  "doc_id": "33190",
  "text": "Treatment for AL includes oral chemotherapy (melphalan and prednisone) or high-dose chemotherapy with autologous stem cell transplantation. The benefit of oral chemotherapy is inadequate, and the greatest survival benefits are limited to patients without cardiac involvement. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Stem cell transplantation has shown promising results for the treatment of primary amyloidosis. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Compared with other hematologic malignancies, transplantrelated mortality is increased 5-fold in amyloidosis. The increased mortality has been attributed to extensive and diffuse systemic endorgan damage from amyloid deposits, and patients with extensive cardiac disease are not optimal candidates for therapy.",
